Budalang&rsquo;i Member of Parliament Ababu Namwamba has hinted at the possibility of working with opposition leader Raila Odinga once more. The lawmaker was speaking in Kisumu when he visited the lakeside city for the first time since resigning as ODM Secretary General. Mr Namwamba said there were no permanent enemies or friends in politics, and added that he has no problem working with Raila in future. Namwamba was attending a prayer meeting at the Voice and Salvation and Healing Church yesterday. He said he intends to unveil a new political party, after which he promised to approach Raila for a partnership. READ MORE Jubilee holding back the country, says Raila Raila Odinga is strongest flagbearer, say ODM chiefs Raila says powerful forces in Jubilee government fighting devolution